{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place 80 g onions, ginger, garlic, coriander, cumin, cardamom, chilli flakes and salt in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Transfer marinade to a large bowl.","Place bowl with marinade on mixing bowl lid and weigh in lamb. Stir well then cover with cling film and place in fridge to marinate for at least 2 hours or overnight.","After this time, place remaining 80 g onions and ghee in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add marinated lamb and, with simmering basket in place of measuring cup, cook <nobr>7 min\/120°C\/\/speed 0.5<\/nobr>.","Add garam masala, tomato purée and yoghurt then, with simmering basket in place of measuring cup, cook <nobr>99 min\/90°C\/\/speed <\/nobr>.","Adjust seasoning to taste then transfer to serving bowls. Top with extra yoghurt and coriander leaves before serving with cooked rice."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["160 g onions, quartered","10 g fresh root ginger, peeled, cut in round slices (2 mm)","3 garlic cloves","2 tsp ground coriander","1 tsp ground cumin","½ tsp ground cardamom","1 tsp dried chilli flakes","1 tsp fine sea salt, plus extra to taste","1000 g lamb shoulder meat, boneless, cubed (3-4 cm)","30 g ghee","1 tsp garam masala","60 g tomato purée","150 g plain yoghurt, plus extra for serving","fresh coriander leaves, for serving","cooked rice, for serving"]}],"id":"r285210","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-cVud1ia5Lfw\/XZQHxX6H25I\/AAAAAAAAcL8\/xlbLb9KUE2Mdu64DUE-BmrPJh8vMDqHbQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_qY3TELhF745RdzOA.png","title":"Lamb Korma","publishedAt":"2018-12-03T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"36 g","fat":"45 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"58 g","calories":"3304 kJ \/ 787 kcal"},"usefulItems":"cling film, large bowl, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["There are so many wonderful flavours associated with Indian cooking, and this mild korma is a great choice when cooking for a family. Slowly simmering the lamb in a creamy and slightly sweet sauce results in beautifully tender meat. Serve with rice, naan breads and your favourite Indian accompaniments."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","4h","6 portions"]}